# Off-nav docs pages — exempt from check-docs-nav-reachable's front-matter floor
# and reachability walk. One repo-relative path per line; '#' comments.
# A page belongs here only when it is off-nav by design: an embedded data
# fragment no link targets, or an immutable dated post that joins no nav by
# derivation either — e.g. the front-matter-less announcement post, rendered
# through jekyll-optional-front-matter (docs/_config.yml), whose inbound links
# are external, not a nav slot. Release notes are NOT listed here: they carry a
# `release:` key, and the Releases page names it in nav_children_key, so each
# note holds a derived nav slot (labeled by its key value) that the gate models.
docs/evidence-data.md
docs/site-architecture.md
docs/posts/2026-07-09-announcing-checkwright.md
